    "title": "LESSON 14: POSSESSIVE PRONOUNS",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Possessive pronouns show ownership:",
          "",
          "mein  = my        unser = our",
          "dein  = your      euer  = your (plural)",
          "sein  = his/its   ihr   = their",
          "ihr   = her       Ihr   = your (formal)",
          "",
          "THEY WORK LIKE 'EIN' (take same endings):",
          "          Masc    Fem     Neut    Plural",
          "NOM:      mein    meine   mein    meine",
          "AKK:      meinen  meine   mein    meine",
          "",
          "EXAMPLES:",
          "Das ist mein Hund. (my dog - masc nom)",
          "Ich sehe deinen Hund. (your dog - masc akk)",
          "Das ist meine Katze. (my cat - fem)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion vierzehn"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "MORE POSSESSIVE EXAMPLES:",
          "",
          "MASCULINE:",
          "Wo ist dein Bruder? (Where is your brother?)",
          "Ich kenne seinen Vater. (I know his father)",
          "",
          "FEMININE:",
          "Das ist meine Schwester. (This is my sister)",
          "Er liebt seine Mutter. (He loves his mother)",
          "",
          "NEUTER:",
          "Wo ist mein Buch? (Where is my book?)",
          "Sie liest ihr Buch. (She reads her book)",
          "",
          "PLURAL:",
          "Das sind unsere Kinder. (These are our children)",
          "Ich mag eure Ideen. (I like your ideas)"
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
]